    <name>
      <text>Complex Number Operations in Trigonometric Form</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Given complex numbers:</p> 
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\( z_1= \displaystyle  {@aa@} (\cos({@angle@})+i\sin({@angle@}))\)</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\( z_2= \displaystyle  {@bb@}(\cos({@angle2@})+i\sin({@angle2@})\))</p>
<p>Calculate in the form \(a+{@%i*b@} \) with \(a, b\) be real numbers;</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; a. \( \displaystyle  z_1&nbsp;\times z_2=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; b. \( \displaystyle \frac{ z_1 }{z_2} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Given complex numbers:</p>
<p>\[ z_1= {@aa@} (\cos({@angle@})+i\sin({@angle@}))\] </p>
<p> \[z_2= {@bb@}(\cos({@angle2@})+i\sin({@angle2@}))\]
<p> (a) Recall : \(A( \cos(\theta)+i\sin(\theta) ) \times B (\cos(\alpha)+i\sin(\alpha)) = (A \times B)(\cos(\theta+\alpha)+i\sin(\theta+\alpha))\)</p>
<p>In this case, the <em>real</em> parts are \( A={@aa@}\) and \(B={@bb@}\), so you need to multiply them. </p>
<p>Then add the angles which are {@angle@} and {@angle2@},</p>
<p>\( \begin{align}
\displaystyle z_{1} \times z_{2} & =  {@aa@}(\cos({@angle@})+i\sin({@angle@})) \times {@bb@} (\cos({@angle2@})+i\sin({@angle2@}) \\
 & = \displaystyle ({@aa@} \times {@bb@})((\cos({@angle@}+{@angle2@})+i\sin({@angle@}+{@angle2@})) \\
& = \displaystyle {@ss@} (\cos({@angle_sum@})+i\sin({@angle_sum@})) \\
& = \displaystyle {@ta@}
\end{align} \)</p>
<p> (b) Recall : For \( \displaystyle \frac{ z_1 }{z_2}=\frac{A(\cos(\theta)+i\sin(\theta))}{B(\cos(\alpha)+i\sin(\alpha))} = \frac{A}{B} (\cos(\theta-\alpha)+i\sin(\theta-\alpha)\)))</p>
<p>Therefore:</p>
<p>\( \begin{align}
\displaystyle \frac{ z_1 }{z_2} & = \frac{{@aa@}(\cos({@angle@})+i\sin({@angle@}))}{ {@bb@} (\cos({@angle2@})+i\sin({@angle2@})} \\
& =  \displaystyle  \left(  \frac{@aa@}{@bb@}\right) \left((\cos({@angle@}-{@angle2@})+i\sin({@angle@}-{@angle2@}) \right) \\
& =  \displaystyle {@ta2@}
\end{align} \)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
